parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the vehicle has difficulty starting
the vehicle has poor engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sensing element can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected engine stalling or running out of fuel, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is inaccurate
the fuel gauge fluctuates or is erratic
the vehicle runs out of fuel despite the gauge indicating otherwise
the fuel sensing element wiring is frayed or charred.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to unexpected engine stalling or running out of fuel, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is inaccurate
the fuel gauge does not move or respond
the fuel gauge is stuck on a particular reading.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause brake fluid to leak, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaking from the brake line
smoke or burning smell coming from the engine compartment
binding
grinding
squealing
or dragging noises from the rear brakes
vehicle pulling to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The binding, grinding, squealing, or dragging of the rear brakes can cause uneven brake wear, reduced brake performance, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Binding
grinding
squealing
or dragging noises from the rear brakes
vehicle pulling to one side while braking
uneven brake wear on the rear brake pads or rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of serious injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite meeting deployment criteria
resulting in potential injury or harm to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or hesitate, leading to reduced acceleration, difficulty shifting gears, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose traction, vibrate, or make unusual noises, leading to reduced vehicle stability, difficulty controlling the vehicle, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
especially at high speeds
the rear differential makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses traction or stability
the rear differential warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
